                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.12/2510: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-03T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 3, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Your despatch 5974. Utilizing the fact that by paragraph Fifth of Protocol of
                    April 1934 Mexican Government agreed to proceed, <pb facs="0776" n="767"
                        xml:id="pg_767"/> at the present stage, with “least possible delay” to
                    conclude the final agreement for the General claims settlement, and the fact
                    that any agreement so concluded must be approved by the Senate, please endeavor
                    to expedite reply to your note of January 13 in an effort to avoid more than a
                    year’s delay in making such agreement effective, since justice to hundreds of
                    claimants, many of them very needy, is meanwhile being deferred.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
